text: Rives-du-Couesnon is a commune in the Ille-et-Vilaine department in Brittany in northwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint-Jean-sur-Couesnon (the seat), Saint-Georges-de- Chesné, Saint-Marc-sur-Couesnon and Vendel.Arrêté préfectoral 17 October 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Ille-et-Vilaine department ==References== Category:Communes of Ille-et-Vilaine Category:States and territories established in 2019
title: Rives-du-Couesnon
